24	1	Managing an unengaged senior designer can be challenging, but it often starts with understanding the root cause of their disengagement. I recommend having an open conversation where you can present constructive feedback while also inviting them to share their perspective. This not only helps align expectations but can also uncover underlying issues that you can address together, fostering a more engaged and empowered designer.	answer	\N	{"knowledge_base_influence": {"sources": [{"id": "chunk_67", "tags": "#management", "title": "Manager or Individual Contributor  (Part 2)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["any", "designer"], "content_snippet": "I recently discussed this with my manager, and they asked me what my choice would be if the company gave me the opportunity to continue working as a design manager/lead or as an individual contributor/product designer", "relevance_score": 36.629999999999995}, {"id": "chunk_140", "tags": "#management, #coaching", "title": "Turning Struggle Into Growth (Part 1)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["any", "designer"], "content_snippet": "In Q1 of 2020, while leading design at Dropbox, I faced one of the more difficult parts of people management: helping a talented designer who was underperforming", "relevance_score": 36.629999999999995}, {"id": "chunk_144", "tags": "#management, #sustainability, #coaching", "title": "Managing Performance With Empathy (Part 1)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["designer"], "content_snippet": "## The Challenge  \\nIn early 2020, I noticed one of my designers struggling", "relevance_score": 33.37}, {"id": "chunk_157", "tags": "#management, #impact, #performance", "title": "From Execution to Strategic Impact   (Part 1)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["designer"], "content_snippet": "## The Challenge  \\nEvery so often, you’ll work with a designer who delivers high-quality solutions at speed", "relevance_score": 18.369999999999997}, {"id": "chunk_159", "tags": "#management, #impact, #performance", "title": "From Execution to Strategic Impact   (Part 3)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["designer"], "content_snippet": "## The Outcome  \\nOver time, the designer began to bring forward new opportunities their PM partner embraced", "relevance_score": 18.369999999999997}, {"id": "chunk_151", "tags": "#design, #productdesign, #impact, #uxr", "title": "Getting Design Involved in Strategy   (Part 2)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["designer"], "content_snippet": "In parallel, I invested in usability tooling and process upgrades, and I carved out time for designers to think beyond incremental changes: one designer dedicated 20% of their time to future-focused work, while the other two committed 10% for two quarters", "relevance_score": 18.369999999999997}, {"id": "chunk_143", "tags": "#management, #coaching", "title": "Turning Struggle Into Growth (Part 4)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["designer"], "content_snippet": "By reframing the work and creating constraints, I was able to help this designer improve in the short term and leave on better terms in the long run", "relevance_score": 18.369999999999997}, {"id": "chunk_124", "tags": "#management, #leadership, #coaching", "title": "Navigating Conflicting Directives\\n (Part 2)", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["any", "senior"], "content_snippet": "A senior architect was advocating for the admin opportunity and had the ear of my boss, partly through past backchannel conversations", "relevance_score": 36.629999999999995}], "avg_relevance": 27.1, "sources_count": 8, "raw_confidence"