42	1	Performance plans can be a critical part of managing underperformance, and I've found that they work best when they're approached with empathy and clarity. It’s essential to first understand the root causes behind the performance issues, whether they’re related to skills, motivation, or external factors. Once you identify those, you can create a structured improvement plan that includes clear goals and regular check-ins, similar to the “[diagnosis, principles, actions](/posts/from-ineffective-to-inspired)” framework I often use. This promotes accountability while also supporting the individual’s growth. The key is to balance the need for improvement with genuine care for the person’s professional journey.	answer	\N	{"user_feedback": {"rating": "thumbs_up", "user_id": 1, "submitted_at": "2025-09-07T22:16:41Z"}, "knowledge_base_influence": {"sources": [{"id": 238, "tags": "#process, #sustainability", "title": "Better Meetings", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["about", "performance"], "content_snippet": "After about 60 minutes of constant video chatting, the brain starts to react as if it’s under stress", "relevance_score": 73.37}, {"id": 263, "tags": "#management, #coaching", "title": "Turning Struggle Into Growth", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["about", "performance"], "content_snippet": "What I Learned This experience taught me that performance management is as much about understanding motivation as it is about addressing skill gaps", "relevance_score": 73.37}, {"id": 264, "tags": "#management, #sustainability, #coaching", "title": "Managing Performance With Empathy", "category": "Blog Post", "confidence": "90.0", "is_framework": false, "word_matches": ["about", "performance"], "content_snippet": "The decline in confidence showed up in reviews as well, leading to a low performance score and eventually a performance plan", "relevance_score": 88.37}, {"